<p><i><b>Altered Carbon</b></i> (2002) is a <a href="/wiki/Hardboiled" title="Hardboiled">hardboiled</a> <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> novel by <a href="/wiki/Richard_K._Morgan" title="Richard K. Morgan" class="mw-redirect">Richard K. Morgan</a>. Set some five hundred years in the future in a universe in which the <a href="/wiki/United_Nations" title="United Nations">United Nations</a> Protectorate oversees a number of <a href="/wiki/Extrasolar_planets" title="Extrasolar planets" class="mw-redirect">extrasolar planets</a> settled by human beings, it features protagonist <a href="/wiki/Takeshi_Kovacs" title="Takeshi Kovacs">Takeshi Kovacs</a>. Kovacs is a former United Nations Envoy and a native of Harlan's World, a planet settled by a Japanese <a href="/wiki/Keiretsu" title="Keiretsu">keiretsu</a> with Eastern European labour.</p>
